http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Tight-security-for-Republic-Day-parade/article14018826.ece

Around 1,000 policemen will guard the parade grounds during the Republic Day celebrations on Tuesday in view of a terror alert issued by the Central Intelligence Agencies.The North Zone police have also taken up massive vehicle checking, lodge checking and cordon and search operation in last few days. Hotel and lodge owners have been asked to inform if they find anything suspicious and at the same time round-the-clock checks to stop anti-socials from taking shelter were being taken up, DCP (north) N. Prakash Reddy said.Those attending the parade have been advised to cooperate and not bring along match boxes, cigars, water bottles and other inflammable material. The police will allow only pass-holders into the premises.